name: Zeus
description: King of the gods and god of thunder, lightning, and the sky.

name: Poseidon
description: God of the sea, earthquakes, and horses.

name: Athena
description: Goddess of wisdom, war, and crafts.

name: Apollo
description: God of music, poetry, prophecy, and the sun.

name: Hera
description: Queen of the gods, goddess of marriage and childbirth.

name: Artemis
description: Goddess of the hunt, wilderness, childbirth, and virginity.

name: Demeter
description: Goddess of agriculture, fertility, and the harvest.

name: Hermes
description: God of commerce, thieves, travelers, and messenger of the gods.

name: Hestia
description: Goddess of the hearth, home, and family.

name: Hades
description: God of the underworld and the dead.

name: Dionysus
description: God of wine, parties, ecstasy.

name: Ra
description: God of the sun, creator of the world, and father of all gods.

name: Osiris
description: God of the afterlife, resurrection, and fertility.

name: Isis
description: Goddess of magic, fertility, motherhood, and rebirth.

name: Horus
description: God of the sky, war, and protection, son of Isis and Osiris.

name: Anubis
description: God of embalming, mummification, and the afterlife.

name: Thoth
description: God of wisdom, writing, and the moon.

name: Bastet
description: Goddess of cats, fertility, and pleasure.

name: Shiva
description: God of destruction and creation, and lord of the dance.

name: Vishnu
description: God of preservation and protection, and one of the three main gods in Hinduism.

name: Brahma
description: God of creation and one of the three main gods in Hinduism.

name: Ganesha
description: God of wisdom, knowledge, and new beginnings, and the remover of obstacles.

name: Kali
description: Goddess of time, change, and destruction.

name: Lakshmi
description: Goddess of wealth, prosperity, and fortune.

name: Odin
description: Chief god of the Aesir, god of wisdom, war, and death.

name: Thor
description: God of thunder, strength, and protection.

name: Loki
description: God of mischief, trickery, and chaos.

name: Freya
description: Goddess of love, fertility, and war.

name: Hel
description: Goddess of the underworld and the dead.

name: Tyr
description: God of law and justice, and patron of warriors.

name: Baldr
description: God of light, beauty, and purity.

name: Heimdall
description: God of light, the senses, and vigilance.
